<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-04-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-04-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-04-11"><hi rend="italic">April 11,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>What progress is being made in settlement of indemnity claims on basis of
                            the Sultan’s promise reported in your telegram of December 9 and your
                            No. 28, of December 12 last year? The President relies implicitly upon
                            His Majesty’s assurances and confidently expects an early adjustment
                            will be reached, as the matter is urgent. Settlement should include all
                            outstanding claims. See my instructions March 25.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
